    en: "A NY car owner whose vehicle is stolen needs to act quickly on three fronts: (1) call 911 or the local police non-emergency line to report the theft, (2) contact the auto insurance carrier to start a comprehensive coverage claim, and (3) notify NY DMV. The police report is required for the insurance claim. NY law classifies unauthorized vehicle taking as a Class A misdemeanor or Class E/D felony depending on the circumstances under Penal Law 165.05 and 165.06. About 40 to 60 percent of stolen vehicles nationally are recovered. If the vehicle is recovered quickly, the owner gets it back (possibly with damage). If not recovered or if damage exceeds value, insurance pays out and title transfers to the insurer. Most theft from a vehicle (radio, GPS, belongings) is covered by comprehensive coverage too but may have a separate deductible."
